# Accessibility floor for frontend UI changes

When adding or modifying interactive UI:

- Interactive elements must have an accessible name and an appropriate role.
- Never encode meaning by color alone. Provide a non-color cue (shape, label, pattern, icon).
- Preserve keyboard accessibility: focusable, operable, and visible focus state.
- Prefer existing component and styling conventions over new abstractions.
- Add or update role-based and name-based tests when practical (query by role and accessible name, not by test id or snapshot).
